   "id": "cell-title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Apple Supply Chain Shock Simulator\n",
    "### A Monte Carlo Simulation grounded in real historical data + live news sentiment\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## What this notebook does\n",
    "\n",
    "Aim of this project:\n",
    "\n",
    "> **If Apple shuts down a cluster of factories representing X% of its total production, how should the stock price react?**\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of guessing the shock size, we:\n",
    "1. Fetch **real Apple stock data** to compute actual volatility\n",
    "2. Measure what Apple's stock **actually did** during 5 historical supply chain events\n",
    "3. Use those real numbers to **calibrate** our simulation\n",
    "4. Fetch **live news headlines** and score their sentiment\n",
    "5. Run **1,000 Monte Carlo simulations** combining all of the above\n",
    "6. Visualise the results as a **5-panel dashboard**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Notebook structure\n",
    "\n",
    "| Section | What it covers |\n",
    "|---------|---------------|\n",
    "| **1. Setup** | Install libraries, imports, global config |\n",
    "| **2. Fetch Apple Data** | Pull real AAPL price history, compute volatility |\n",
    "| **3. Historical Shock Calibration** | Measure real past events, derive calibrated shock |\n",
    "| **4. News Sentiment Analysis** | Scrape headlines, score with NLP |\n",
    "| **5. Monte Carlo Simulation** | Run 1,000 GBM price paths |\n",
    "| **6. Visualisation** | 5-panel dashboard |\n",
    "| **7. Results & Interpretation** | What the numbers actually mean |"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-section-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 1 — Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "First we install the libraries we need and set up our global configuration.\n",
    "\n",
    "All the key assumptions — factory share, number of simulations, sentiment weighting — live in one `CONFIG` dictionary so they are easy to find and change.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Try changing `factory_share`** to see how a bigger or smaller factory affects the result."
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-setup-install",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install dependencies (only needed once — safe to re-run)\n",
