  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-section-4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 4 — News Sentiment Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Markets don't just react to facts — they react to **how those facts are reported**. Negative headlines accelerate selloffs. Positive headlines cushion them.\n",
    "\n",
    "We capture this by:\n",
    "1. Scraping live Apple headlines from **Google News RSS** (free, no API key)\n",
    "2. Scoring each headline using **TextBlob** — a simple NLP library that assigns a polarity score from `-1` (very negative) to `+1` (very positive)\n",
    "3. Computing a **composite sentiment score** across all headlines\n",
    "4. Using that score to nudge the simulation shock slightly up or down\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Note:** TextBlob is a general-purpose NLP model, not finance-specific. A more advanced version of this project could use **FinBERT** — a model trained specifically on financial text."
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-fetch-headlines",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def fetch_headlines(n=20):\n",
    "    url = 'https://news.google.com/rss/search?q=Apple+AAPL+stock&hl=en-US&gl=US&ceid=US:en'\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        resp = requests.get(url, headers={'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0'}, timeout=10)\n",
    "        soup = BeautifulSoup(resp.content, 'xml')\n",
    "        items = soup.find_all('item')[:n]\n",
    "        return [{\n",
    "            'title':   item.find('title').text  if item.find('title')  else '',\n",
    "            'source':  item.find('source').text if item.find('source') else 'Unknown',\n",
    "        } for item in items]\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f'Could not fetch live headlines ({e}) — using sample data.')\n",
    "        return [\n",
    "            {'title': 'Apple beats earnings expectations with record services revenue', 'source': 'Reuters'},\n",
    "            {'title': 'iPhone demand in China shows signs of recovery analysts say',    'source': 'Bloomberg'},\n",
    "            {'title': 'Apple supplier warns of production delays amid trade tensions',   'source': 'FT'},\n",
    "            {'title': 'Apple faces regulatory scrutiny in EU over App Store policies',   'source': 'WSJ'},\n",
    "            {'title': 'Analysts raise Apple price target on strong services growth',     'source': 'CNBC'},\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "\n",
    "headlines = fetch_headlines(20)\n",
    "print(f'Fetched {len(headlines)} headlines.\\n')\n",
    "for h in headlines[:5]:\n",
    "    print(f\"  [{h['source'][:15]:<15}] {h['title'][:70]}\")"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-sentiment-score",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Score each headline\n",
    "scored = []\n",
    "for h in headlines:\n",
    "    blob = TextBlob(h['title'])\n",
    "    scored.append({**h, 'polarity': blob.sentiment.polarity})\n",
    "\n",
    "sent_df   = pd.DataFrame(scored)\n",
    "composite = sent_df['polarity'].mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Map composite to a shock modifier\n",
    "# e.g. -0.3 composite → adds roughly -1.5% to the shock\n",
    "sentiment_modifier = composite * 0.05\n",
    "\n",
    "CONFIG['_sentiment']          = composite\n",
    "CONFIG['_sentiment_modifier'] = sentiment_modifier\n",
    "CONFIG['_sent_df']            = sent_df\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Composite sentiment score : {composite:+.3f}')\n",
    "print(f'Shock modifier            : {sentiment_modifier:+.2%}')\n",
    "print(f\"\\nPositive headlines : {(sent_df['polarity'] >  0.05).sum()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Neutral headlines  : {((sent_df['polarity'] >= -0.05) & (sent_df['polarity'] <= 0.05)).sum()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Negative headlines : {(sent_df['polarity'] < -0.05).sum()}\")"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-plot-sentiment",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualise headline sentiment\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 5))\n",
    "s_sorted = sent_df.sort_values('polarity').reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "s_colors = ['#c0392b' if p < -0.05 else ('#1d9e75' if p > 0.05 else '#aaaaaa')\n",
    "            for p in s_sorted['polarity']]\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.barh(range(len(s_sorted)), s_sorted['polarity'], color=s_colors,\n",
    "        alpha=0.85, edgecolor='none', height=0.6)\n",
    "ax.set_yticks(range(len(s_sorted)))\n",
    "ax.set_yticklabels([t[:35] + '…' if len(t) > 35 else t\n",
    "                    for t in s_sorted['title']], fontsize=8)\n",
    "ax.axvline(0, color='#333', linewidth=0.8)\n",
    "ax.axvline(composite, color='#185fa5', linewidth=1.5,\n",
    "           linestyle='--', label=f'Composite: {composite:+.3f}')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Polarity score  (−1 = very bearish, +1 = very bullish)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Apple Headline Sentiment Analysis', fontsize=12)\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(-1.0, 1.0)\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "ax.set_facecolor('white')\n",
    "ax.grid(alpha=0.2, axis='x')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-section-5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 5 — Monte Carlo Simulation\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we combine everything into the simulation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### The model: Geometric Brownian Motion (GBM)\n",
    "\n",
    "GBM is the standard mathematical model for stock prices. The key idea is that each day's return has two components:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "return = drift × dt  +  volatility × √dt × Z\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Where:\n",
    "- **drift** = average daily return (from real data)\n",
    "- **volatility** = how jumpy the stock is (from real data)\n",
    "- **Z** = a random draw from a normal distribution — the \"randomness\" part\n",
    "- **dt** = 1/252 (one trading day as a fraction of a year)\n",
    "\n",
    "### The shock\n",
    "\n",
    "On **day 1 only**, we add our combined shock:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "final_shock = calibrated_shock + sentiment_modifier\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "After day 1, the stock evolves naturally according to GBM — the market processes the news and moves on."
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-compute-final-shock",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Combine calibrated shock + sentiment modifier\n",
    "final_shock = CONFIG['_calibrated_shock'] + CONFIG['_sentiment_modifier']\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Shock breakdown:')\n",
    "print(f\"  Calibrated shock (from history) : {CONFIG['_calibrated_shock']:+.2%}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Sentiment modifier              : {CONFIG['_sentiment_modifier']:+.2%}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  ─────────────────────────────────────────\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Final shock applied on day 1    : {final_shock:+.2%}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "CONFIG['_final_shock'] = final_shock"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-run-simulation",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def run_monte_carlo(S0, drift, vol, shock, n_sims, n_days):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Geometric Brownian Motion simulation.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns a matrix of shape (n_days+1, n_sims)\n",
    "    where each column is one simulated price path.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    dt = 1 / 252\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Random draws: one per day per simulation\n",
    "    Z = np.random.standard_normal((n_days, n_sims))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Daily log returns via GBM formula\n",
    "    daily_returns = (drift - 0.5 * vol**2) * dt + vol * np.sqrt(dt) * Z\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Apply supply shock on day 1 (announcement day)\n",
    "    daily_returns[0] += shock\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Compound returns into price paths\n",
    "    price_paths = S0 * np.exp(np.cumsum(daily_returns, axis=0))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Prepend starting price so paths begin at S0\n",
    "    return np.vstack([np.full(n_sims, S0), price_paths])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Running {CONFIG['n_simulations']:,} simulations over {CONFIG['n_days']} trading days...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "price_paths = run_monte_carlo(\n",
    "    S0    = CONFIG['_S0'],\n",
    "    drift = CONFIG['_drift'],\n",
    "    vol   = CONFIG['_vol'],\n",
    "    shock = CONFIG['_final_shock'],\n",
    "    n_sims= CONFIG['n_simulations'],\n",
    "    n_days= CONFIG['n_days'],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Done. Output shape: {price_paths.shape}  (days × simulations)')"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-summary-stats",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Summary statistics\n",
    "final  = price_paths[-1, :]\n",
    "S0     = CONFIG['_S0']\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=' * 48)\n",
    "print('  SIMULATION RESULTS — 1 YEAR OUTLOOK')\n",
    "print('=' * 48)\n",
    "print(f\"  Starting price        : ${S0:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Median outcome (P50)  : ${np.percentile(final, 50):.2f}\")\n",
